      • executeCommand

        void executeCommand(java.lang.String command)
             throws InvalidCommandException,
                    InvalidPositionException
        Executes a list of commands, the commands can be:

        L - Move robot facing to left R - Move robot facing to right M - Move robot forward (to the direction of the facing)

        Parameters:
        command - The string with the commands
        Throws:
        InvalidCommandException - If unknown characters are sent in the string.
        InvalidPositionException - If robot is instructed to move outside bounds.
